# Strategy Pattern

All pluggable behavior uses the Strategy pattern: define an interface, implement it per vendor, select via factory.

## Structure

```
services/
  ticket-system/
    strategy.ts       ← interface + shared types
    youtrack.ts       ← YouTrack implementation
    jira.ts           ← future: Jira implementation
    factory.ts        ← creates the right strategy from config
```

## Rules

- The interface is the contract. Every implementation must satisfy it fully — no optional methods, no partial implementations.
- Consumers depend only on the interface, never on a concrete implementation.
- The factory is the only place that knows about concrete classes.
- New integrations = new file implementing the interface + one line in the factory. Never modify existing implementations.
- Each strategy method should be stateless where possible — receive what it needs via parameters.

## Adding a New Strategy

1. Create `apps/api/src/services/ticket-system/{name}.ts` implementing `TicketSystemStrategy`.
2. Add the new type to the `TicketSystemType` enum in `packages/shared/src/enums.ts` and Prisma schema.
3. Add one case to the factory switch in `factory.ts`.
4. Done — no other files change.
